subSubSection.paragraph:
Description of 
holotype
(
Fig. 3
).

Adult male, SVL 
24.5 mm
(
Fig. 3
); head longer than wide (HL/HW=1.14); snout shorter than wide (SL/SW=0.84), projecting beyond lower jaw, weakly tuberculate, truncate in dorsal view, truncate and sloping in lateral view (
Fig. 3B
); canthus rostralis distinct, lores vertical, flat; nares open anterolaterally just below canthus, located much closer to end of snout than to eye; keratinized submandibular spinules present; distance between nares smaller than snout length (IND/SL=0.71) and snout width (IND/SW=0.59); eyes large, protruding beyond upper jaws in ventral view (
Fig. 3C
), diameter less than snout length (ED/SL=0.87) and interorbital distance (ED/IOD=1.08); pupils horizontal; interorbital region flat, weakly tuberculate, distance smaller than snout width (IOD/SW=0.68) and snout length (IOD/SL=0.81); tympanum distinct, suboval, taller than wide (
Fig. 3
), horizontal axis less than eye diameter (TD/ED=0.70); choanae subcircular, separated by a distance larger than their diameter; vomerine ridges and teeth absent; tongue narrow, ending in median point, posterior one-half free.
